
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `gnome-font-viewer` baraye didan va barrasi font-ha (fonts) dar mohit GNOME be kar miravad. Ba in dastoor, mitoonid font-ha ro bebinid, mesal-ha az matn ba anha neveshte va vizhegi-haye font ro check konid.  

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `gnome-font-viewer [FILE]`  --> 📁 Baz kardane font az yek file. Agar file name dade nashe, font viewer khali baz mishe.
    🔹 `gnome-font-viewer --help`  --> ❓ Namayesh dadane rahnamaye dastoor.
    🔹 `gnome-font-viewer --version` --> ℹ️ Namayesh dadane version e barname.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ gnome-font-viewer /usr/share/fonts/truetype/dejavu/DejaVuSans.ttf

    🔹 Baz kardane font "DejaVuSans.ttf" az masir mored nazar.

    $ gnome-font-viewer

    🔹 Baz kardane barnameye font viewer be soorat khali, ke shoma betoonid az dakhel barname font ha ro baz konid.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ gnome-font-viewer --version

    🔹 Namayesh version e `gnome-font-viewer`. Az in dastoor estefade konid ta motmaen shavid barname sahih nasb shode va az che versioni estefade mikonid.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `gnome-font-viewer` command is used to view and inspect fonts in the GNOME environment. It allows you to see how fonts look, preview text examples, and check font properties.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `gnome-font-viewer [FILE]`  --> 📁 Opens a font from a specified file. If no file is specified, the font viewer opens empty.
    🔹 `gnome-font-viewer --help`  --> ❓ Displays help information about the command.
    🔹 `gnome-font-viewer --version` --> ℹ️ Displays the version number of the program.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ gnome-font-viewer /usr/share/fonts/truetype/dejavu/DejaVuSans.ttf

    🔹 Opens the "DejaVuSans.ttf" font from the specified path.

    $ gnome-font-viewer

    🔹 Opens the font viewer application in an empty state, allowing you to open fonts from within the application.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ gnome-font-viewer --version

    🔹 Displays the version of `gnome-font-viewer`. Use this command to verify that the program is correctly installed and to know which version you are using.
